# Fix Light & Dark Mode UI and Functional Bugs

This plan addresses the UI contrast/visibility issues in Light and Dark modes, missing color scales, and potential functional bugs across the application.

## Open Questions
- Is there any specific missing link or button you've experienced issues with that is not listed in the functional bugs section below?
- Are you okay with me replacing hardcoded colors (`bg-white/70`, `text-black/55`) with semantic theme variables (`bg-card`, `text-muted-foreground`) to guarantee flawless switching between modes?

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration & Global CSS

#### [MODIFY] [globals.css](file:///d:/Projects/Liya/app/globals.css)
- Add missing `--color-liya-*` and `--color-ink` scales to `@theme`.
- Enable class-based dark mode in Tailwind v4 by adding `@custom-variant dark (&:is(.dark *));`. This single line fixes the issue where `dark:text-white` fails to apply when switching themes.
- Update semantic variables (`--background`, `--foreground`, `--card`, etc.) to use valid Hex/RGB colors instead of raw HSL values, as Tailwind v4 requires valid CSS colors in `@theme`.
- Add dark mode inversions for all semantic variables in `.dark`.

### Component Refactoring

I will refactor the following components to replace hardcoded utility classes (e.g., `bg-white/70`, `text-black/55`) with semantic tokens (e.g., `bg-card`, `text-muted-foreground`). This will eliminate all text visibility issues and ensure components automatically adapt to themes.

